EMMY-NOMINATED actress Thuso Mbedu has shared teasers of The Underground Railroad, which she stars in. Thuso made headlines last year when she was cast for the American series as the lead. She shared the first teasers of the series on Instagram. The videos don’t show much, but they give you a glimpse of what the story is about. Thuso stars as Cora Randall, a slave who is on a quest for freedom. After running away from the Georgia plantation she worked at for the rumoured Underground Railroad, Cora discovers it. The show is directed by Barry Jenkins, acclaimed director of the Oscar-winning films “Moonlight” and “If Beale Street Could Talk. ALSO READ: IDOLS STAR PHINDY DUBE IS PREGNANT! She finds that it’s an actual railroad full of engineers and conductors, and a secret network of tracks and tunnels beneath the Southern soil. The series is based The Underground Railroad, the novel by Colson Whitehead. Acting alongside Thuso in the two-part series are actors Chase W. Dillon and Joel Edgerton. The release date has not been announced yet. So @bandrybarry released ANOTHER teaser ?? Y’all aren’t ready for #THEUNDERGROUNDRAILROAD coming soon to @amazonstudios ?? A post shared by  Thuso Mbedu (@thuso.mbedu) on Oct 21, 2020 at 10:17am PDT